            body: '<p>Elon Reeve Musk was born in Pretoria, South Africa, on June 28, 1971. He is one of the most influential entrepreneurs in history, building or leading companies that have transformed the automotive, space exploration, artificial intelligence, and social media industries.</p><p>His entrepreneurial journey began with selling Zip2 for $307 million (1999), then founding X.com — which became PayPal and was sold to eBay for $1.5 billion (2002). He went on to found SpaceX (2002) and joined Tesla Motors (2004), eventually becoming its CEO and majority shareholder.</p><p>In June 2026, SpaceX completed its IPO at $135 per share, valuing the company at approximately $1.5 trillion — one of the largest IPOs in history. In February 2026, he merged SpaceX with his AI startup xAI, creating a super-entity valued at over $1 trillion. He also restructured xAI into four separate business units in mid-2026.</p><p>Politically, he briefly served as head of the Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) under the Trump administration before resigning to focus on business. His net worth is estimated to exceed $300 billion, maintaining his position as the world\'s richest person.</p>',
