            body: '<p>Taylor Alison Swift was born in West Reading, Pennsylvania, on December 13, 1989. She is an American singer-songwriter, musician, and actress who has become one of the best-selling music artists of all time.</p><p>Her career began in Nashville as a teenage country artist before expanding far beyond genre boundaries. Her self-titled debut album (2006) was an instant success, and she continued to dominate charts with albums including Fearless, 1989, Reputation, Folklore, Evermore, Midnights, The Tortured Poets Department, and The Life of a Showgirl (2025) — her 15th consecutive No.1 album on the Billboard 200, which also set a new all-time record for largest weekly streaming numbers.</p><p>On June 12, 2026, she made history by becoming the youngest woman ever inducted into the Songwriters Hall of Fame at age 36, breaking a record previously held by Carole King by nearly a decade. Forbes ranked her #23 on its 2026 America\'s Richest Self-Made Women list.</p>',
